# Common Gateway Interface (CGI)
  Used to create HTML Content
  
  Scripts are written in C, Python, Ruby, Pearl
  
  # Apache Web server uses the ScriptAlias directive CGI scripts location
  # Selinux limits running CGI scripts 
  # Script Directories need a special security context
  # Scripts run as the Apache user
  
 # CGI scripts common uses:
 
 - Gather input from the user
 - Query or update databases
 - Email
 - Run system commands
 
 
 
  
